   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR SOME IMPORTANT ITEMS OF THE TRUTH THAT HAVE BEEN MISUNDERSTOOD 1 Scripture Reading: 1 Tim 1:4; Eph 3:9-11; 1:9-10; 3:2-4; Col 1:25-27; Eph 3:8; 2 Cor 13:14; Eph 3:10; 1:23; 3:19 OUTLINE Some important items of the truth that have been misunderstood: God's economy 1 Tim 1:4: God's household administration, arrangement, and plan Eph 3:9-11.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The stewardship of God's household administration: Understanding the mystery of Christ the church Eph 3:2-4.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Completing the word of God, that is, the mystery which has been hidden from the ages and from the generations, the glory of which is Christ in the believers, the hope of glory Col 1:25-27.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Preaching to people the unsearchable riches of Christ Eph 3:8.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God's dispensing: The goal of God's economy.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In the rich operation of the Triune God, to dispense the unsearchable riches of Christ to the believers Eph 3:8; 2 Cor 13:14.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>For the producing of the church Eph 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To become the fullness of Christ and the fullness of God, to be the expression of God Eph 1:23; 3:19.</S>
   </TEXT>
